PRESS DIGEST - Washington Post business - Dec 20 . The Washington Post carried the following business stories on December 20 : - - - NEW YORK - Stocks shot higher on the back of a big bond market rally with the Dow Jones industrial average surging nearly 127 points . - - - WASHINGTON - Throughout the charity industry , efforts to tap the holiday spirit through solicitations are increasing . - - - WASHINGTON - Spot shortages of some goods , particularly bakery and dairy items , appeared at some area of Giant Food Inc stores as a strike by truck delivery workers entered its sixth day . - - - NEW YORK - Former bond trader Joseph Jett , accused of triggering the collapse of Kidder , Peabody & Co with an alleged $ 350 million securities fraud , won a major victory when an arbitration panel ruled against requiring him to pay damages to the company . 
